.SH NAME
.PP
cati \- monitor a process and trigger a catification
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
cati [flags] [utility [args\&...]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Never sit and wait for some long\-running process to finish.
CATI can alert you when it's done.
You can receive messages on your computer or phone.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-t <string>, \-\-title <string>
Set catification title.
Default is utility name.
.RS
.RE
.TP
.B \-m <string>, \-\-message <string>
Set catification message.
Default is \[lq]Done!\[rq].
.RS
.RE
.TP
.B \-b, \-\-banner
Trigger a banner catification.
This is enabled by default.
To disable this service, set this flag to false.
This will be either \f[C]nsuser\f[], \f[C]freedesktop\f[], or
\f[C]catifyicon\f[] catification, depending on the OS.
.RS
.RE
.TP
.B \-s, \-\-speech
Trigger a speech catification.
This will be either \f[C]say\f[], \f[C]espeak\f[], or
\f[C]speechsynthesizer\f[] catification, depending on the OS.
.RS
.RE
.TP
.B \-c, \-\-bearychat
Trigger a BearyChat catification.
This requires \f[C]bearychat.incomingHookURI\f[] to be set.
.RS
.RE
.TP
.B \-i, \-\-hipchat
Trigger a HipChat catification.
This requires \f[C]hipchat.accessToken\f[] and \f[C]hipchat.room\f[] to
be set.
.RS
.RE
.TP
.B \-p, \-\-pushbullet
Trigger a Pushbullet catification.
This requires \f[C]pushbullet.accessToken\f[] to be set.
.RS
.RE
.TP
.B \-o, \-\-pushover
Trigger a Pushover catification.
This requires \f[C]pushover.apiToken\f[] and \f[C]pushover.userKey\f[]
to be set.
.RS
.RE
.TP
.B \-u, \-\-pushsafer
Trigger a Pushsafer catification.
This requires \f[C]pushsafer.key\f[] to be set.
.RS
.RE
.TP
.B \-l, \-\-simplepush
Trigger a Simplepush catification.
This requires \f[C]simplepush.key\f[] to be set.
.RS
.RE
.TP
.B \-k, \-\-slack
Trigger a Slack catification.
This requires \f[C]slack.token\f[] and \f[C]slack.channel\f[] to be set.
.RS
.RE
.TP
.B \-w , \-\-pwatch 
Monitor a process by PID and trigger a catification when the pid
disappears.
.RS
.RE
.TP
.B \-f, \-\-file
Path to \f[C]cati.yaml\f[] configuration file.
.RS
.RE
.TP
.B \-\-verbose
Enable verbose mode.
.RS
.RE
.TP
.B \-v, \-\-version
Print \f[C]cati\f[] version and exit.
.RS
.RE
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Print \f[C]cati\f[] help and exit.
.RS
.RE
