.SH FILES
.PP
If not explicitly set with \-\-file, then cati will check the following
paths, in the following order.
.IP \[bu] 2
\&./.cati.yaml
.IP \[bu] 2
$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/cati/cati.yaml
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Display a catification when \f[C]tar\f[] finishes compressing files.
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
cati\ tar\ \-cjf\ music.tar.bz2\ Music/
\f[]
.fi
.PP
Add cati after a command, in case you forgot at the beginning.
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
clang\ foo.c\ \-Wall\ \-lm\ \-L/usr/X11R6/lib\ \-lX11\ \-o\ bizz;\ cati
\f[]
.fi
.PP
If you already started a command, but forgot to use \f[C]cati\f[], then
you can do this to get catified when that process' PID disappears.
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
cati\ \-\-pwatch\ $(pgrep\ docker\-machine)
\f[]
.fi
